From: tzs@stein3.u.washington.edu (Tim Smith)
Subject: Re: Is there a better vi?
Date: 18 Oct 1993 02:28:04 GMT

Roger C. Pao <rpao@mts.mivj.ca.us> wrote:
>>The Ctrl-Shift stuff is not real vi, since they are not normal Unix
>>keying. To switch between multiple files you have:
>
>The actual key sequence is Ctrl-6.  In any case, it works on "Version
>SVR4.0", but not on the Linux supplied vi.  "Version SVR4.0" comes from
>typing ":ver".

It also works on Ultrix, whose vi claims to be version 3.7, 18-Oct-85,
and on A/UX, whose vi claims to be version 3.9, 2/9/83 (!).

The character needed is ASCII 036, which, logically, would be Ctrl-^
(or maybe Ctrl-~).  Ctrl-6 probably works because the keyboard realizes
that Ctrl-6 makes no sense, and so assumes you want Ctrl-^ (I'm assuming
your ^ is on your 6 key).

--Tim Smith

