From: imcclogh@cs.ucsd.edu (Ian McCloghrie)
Subject: Re: Which UART for fast (14.4) modem?
Date: 18 Oct 93 03:32:12 GMT

danny@dragon.stgt.sub.org (Daniel T. Schwager) writes:

>gast@cs.ucla.edu wrote:

>: Is a 16550 UART recommended or is it not needed?

>i have  a normal 16450 UART and a 16.8 Zyxel modem. It works
>great !

        It depends upon how fast your system is.  Basically, if you've
got a 16550, your CPU is servicing fewer interrupts at any given
serial speed.  If you've got a 486DX2/66 then you may never notice
the difference.  If yuo've got a 386SX/16, on the other hand, it's a
godsend.  In any case, given that a 16550 serial card costs about $30,
I think it's well worth the investment for anyone getting a 14.4 modem.

