From: imcclogh@cs.ucsd.edu (Ian McCloghrie)
Crossposted-To: comp.os.linux.help
Subject: Re: Linux file system standard
Date: 18 Oct 93 03:38:40 GMT

p00784@psilink.com (Joe Morris) writes:

>>FROM:   Joseph Womack - EECS <jwomack@yoda.eecs.wsu.edu>
>>I need to find the most recent file system standards. 

>I get the feelin that a lot of things are happening through the mailing
>lists, of which I know little. Could someone post currently active mailing
>lists? and post-masters there-of. I'm finally at the point where I could
>help out.

>BTW, the most recent File_System_Standard I saw was from 1992

        The main linux mailing list (linux-activists@niksula.hut.fi)
has multiple "channels" (really sub-lists).  There's around 2 dozen of
these channels, as I recall, NORMAL, NET, KERNEL, FSSTND.  FSSTND
is a bunch of folk writing a draft filesystem layout.  It's not finished
as yet, so you won't find it up for ftp.  If you're interested in helping
out, join the mailing list.

